首先，我们可以利用下面两个等式来rewrite the given limit:

$$\begin{aligned}
\lim_{x\to 0}\frac{\sqrt{1+x\cos x}-\sqrt{1+\sin x}}{x^3}
&= \lim_{x\to 0}\frac{\sqrt{1+x\cos x}-\sqrt{1+x\sin x}}{x^3} \\
&= \lim_{x\to 0}\frac{\sqrt{1+x\cos x-\sin x}}{x^3}
\end{aligned}$$

现在，我们可以使用 Taylor series expansion of $\sqrt{1+u}$ about $u=0$ to rewrite the numerator and denominator:

$$\begin{aligned}
\lim_{x\to 0}\frac{\sqrt{1+x\cos x-\sin x}}{x^3}
&= \lim_{x\to 0}\frac{\sqrt{1+x\cos x-\sin x}}{x^3} \\
&= \lim_{x\to 0}\frac{1+x\cos x-\sin x}{x^3} \\
&= \lim_{x\to 0}\left(1-\frac{\sin x}{x}\right) \\
&= 1-\lim
